This is a lovely soup, but I did make some changes (which bring it up to a 4-fork rating for me!) I added a clove of minced garlic to the onion stage, and used only 1 tbl of fat (butter.) I used a scant 1/2 tsp of grated orange zest instead of OJ, then for the half and half I used 1/4 cup of fat-free half and half and 1/4 cup of buttermilk. Virtually no fat and tastes better! The tartness of the buttermilk is perfect with this soup! Might try all buttermilk next time. Also, I used nutmeg (as previously suggested) in place of the cinnamon - fresh grated! YUM.

